Gunmen have kidnapped the wife of a member of the Jigawa State House of Assembly. Hajiya Zahra’u Haruna was abducted in the early hours of Saturday at her residence Dangyatum village in Jahun local government area of the state. Her husband, Haruna Dangyatun, represents Miga constituency. The Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO) in the state, SP Abdu Jinjiri, told NAN that Hajiya Zahra’u Haruna, was kidnapped by   three gunmen at about 4 a.m. “Three unknown men came to the residence of victim with dane guns and cutlasses and took her to an unknown destination,” Jinjiri said. But the police are already giving the suspects a hot chase.”